devdoc.details: We can consider this contract as a master contract that contains no actual business logic but enforces permission checks and delegates function calls to corresponding libraries. Although contract states are defined in libraries, they are initialized and stored in this contract.

params.collateralAmount: The collateral amount to be added to the loan (overwritten by msg.value if collateral token is ETH)

returns.totalCollateralAmount: The total collateral amount after adding collateral

returns.withdrewAmount: Total amount withdrew, not including interest

params.loanId: ID that identifies the loan record

getMaxLoanTerm().details: Remove documentation of return parameters in order to compile

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.repayAmount: Amount to repay (overwritten by msg.value if loan token is ETH)

params.collateralAmount: The collateral amount to be subtracted from the loan

returns.totalCollateralAmount: The total collateral amount after subtracting collateral

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

disableDepositToken(address).notice: Disable an token, i.e., ERC20 token, for deposit

enableDepositToken(address).notice: Enable an ERC20 token for deposit

getDepositTokens().notice: Return details for each deposit token

getLoanInterestRate(address,uint256).notice: Return loan interest rate for given token

getLoanRecordById(bytes32).notice: Return basic info of a loan record

getLoanRecordsByAccount(address).notice: Return details of all loans owned by the caller

getMaxDistributorFeeRatios().notice: Return the maximum fee ratio for distributors

getTokenPrice(address).notice: Return USD price of a token

isDepositEarlyWithdrawable(bytes32).notice: Return whether a deposit can be early withdrew.

removeLoanAndCollateralTokenPair(address.notice: Remove a loan and collateral token pair, e.g., ETH_DAI

repayLoan(bytes32,uint256).notice: Pay back a specific amount of loan

setBalanceCap(address,uint256).notice: Set balance cap for a token

setInterestReserveAddress(address).notice: Set interest reserve address, which receives protocol reserve.

setLoanAndCollateralTokenPair(address,ad.notice: Set a loan and collateral token pair, e.g., ETH_DAI.

setMaxDistributorFeeRatios(uint256,uint2.notice: Set the maximum fee ratio for distributors

setProtocolReserveRatio(uint256).notice: Set protocol reserve ratio, which determines the percentage         of interest that goes to protocol reserve.
